curam.util.persistence.helper

Class LifecycleStateTransitionEventDefaultListener<S,L extends Lifecycle<S>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • curam.util.persistence.helper.LifecycleStateTransitionEventDefaultListener<S,L>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - The class which communicates the state.
    L - The class whose lifecycle is being managed.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    LifecycleStateTransitionEvent<S,L>

    public abstract class LifecycleStateTransitionEventDefaultListener<S,L extends Lifecycle<S>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements LifecycleStateTransitionEvent<S,L>
    The default listener for lifecycle state transition events. Allows concrete implementations to listener to some events without having to provide empty listener methods for other events.

                    throws InformationalException
        Called after a state transition has occurred..

      • pretransition

        public boolean pretransition(L subject,
                             S oldState,
                             S newState)
                      throws InformationalException
        Called before a state transition is about to occur..
        Specified by:
        pretransition in interface LifecycleStateTransitionEvent<S,L extends Lifecycle<S>>
        Parameters:
        subject - The object whose state is about to change.
        oldState - The state that the object is about to transition from (as currently stored on the database, null if the object is about to be inserted).
        newState - The state that the object is about to transition to (null if the object is about to be deleted).
        Returns:
        True if the listener approves the transition to go ahead, false if the listener asks to interrupt the transition.
        Throws:
        InformationalException - if the listener vetoes the transition.
